// main.fitz — orchestrator for the Admin ABM showcase (Slice 1).
//
// Wires the feature modules into one server:
//   - auth.fitz       → GET/POST /login, GET /logout (session cookie).
//   - dashboard.fitz  → GET / , /empleados, /departamentos (protected).
//
// `import <module>` is enough for the runtime/codegen to plug each module's
// HTTP handlers into the router (W16 cross-module). The server binds on
// 0.0.0.0 so it works both under `fitz run` and inside Docker.
//
// The database schema + demo seed live in `db/init.sql` (run by Postgres on
// first boot, or with `psql -f db/init.sql` locally). The app never touches
// the schema at boot and only connects during requests — see db/init.sql
// for why. So there's nothing to run here at startup: just serve.
//
// Slice 2 adds the live WebSocket layer: `empleados.fitz` serves the
// Empleados DataGrid over `/empleados` (SSR first paint) + `/live/empleados`
// (WS pagination). The rest stays SSR.

import auth
import dashboard
import empleados

@server(3000, "0.0.0.0")
fn main() => 0

print("[ready] Admin ABM — http://127.0.0.1:3000/")
print("[ready] login demo: admin@fitz.dev / admin1234")
print("[ready] routes: /login  /  /empleados (live)  /departamentos  /logout")
